topics.body:
My mom got herself *TWO* Galaxy Note S3s due to investments and insurance.
I get to keep one while my sister keeps the other.
At first, I was so excited but then I noticed that my SIM card was a Mini.
The phone required a Micro SIM to function.

After I nearly lost all hope, I checked the Internet, took the measurements and trimmed my SIM card using nothing but a pair of fabric scissors, a nail file, a 0.01 mm scale ruler and an extremely sharp pencil.

After 10 minutes of measuring and trimming, I finally got my Micro SIM card! And it works!

*YEAH!*
